---
title: Checkboxes
---
p.-text Checboxes are used to select one or several options in a list.

h3 Examples
p.-text
  | To render a checkbox, apply the class <code>a-input</code> to an <code>input type="checkbox"</code>.
  | For proper styling, checkboxes require an empty label element defined immediately after their declaration.

h4 Stacked
p.-text
  | Group checkboxes in <code>a-formGroup</code> for easy stacking.
.example.-mb3
  .-p3
    .a-formGroup
      input(type="checkbox", class="a-input", id="checkbox1")
      label(for="checkbox1")
      label.-text(for="checkbox1") Checkbox
    .a-formGroup
      input(type="checkbox", class="a-input", id="checkbox2", disabled)
      label(for="checkbox2")
      label.-text(for="checkbox2") Disabled Checkbox
  :code(lang="html")
    <div class="a-formGroup">
      <input type="checkbox" class="a-input" id="checkbox1">
      <label for="checkbox1"></label>
      <label class="-text" for="checkbox1">Checkbox</label>
    </div>
    <div class="a-formGroup">
      <input type="checkbox" class="a-input" id="checkbox2" disabled>
      <label for="checkbox2"></label>
      <label class="-text" for="checkbox2">Disabled Checkbox</label>
    </div>

h4 Inline
p.-text
  | Apply the class <code>-inline</code> to <code>a-formGroup</code> to display checkboxes inline.
.example.-mb3
  .-p3
    .a-formGroup.-inline
      input(type="checkbox", class="a-input", id="inlineCheckbox1")
      label(for="inlineCheckbox1")
      label.-text(for="inlineCheckbox1") Option 1
    .a-formGroup.-inline.-ml1
      input(type="checkbox", class="a-input", id="inlineCheckbox2")
      label(for="inlineCheckbox2")
      label.-text(for="inlineCheckbox2") Option 2
  :code(lang="html")
    <div class="a-formGroup -inline">
      <input type="checkbox" class="a-input" id="inlineCheckbox1">
      <label for="inlineCheckbox1"></label>
      <label class="-text" for="inlineCheckbox1">Option 1</label>
    </div>
    <div class="a-formGroup -inline">
      <input type="checkbox" class="a-input" id="inlineCheckbox2">
      <label for="inlineCheckbox2"></label>
      <label class="-text" for="inlineCheckbox2">Option 2</label>
    </div>
